In England, in the seven days to 14 May, there were 48,830 new confirmed cases (86.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 07 May, there were 61,309 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 20% (12,479 fewer cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 19 May is 18,695,641 (33,060.3 cases per 100,000 population).
